{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"367b4d8e-4f0f-45e6-a3b5-13d1e3f4280a","content":"The directory appears empty, so I'll answer from my knowledge:\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Why this is enough:** Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. Setting `UseVSTest` to `true` was opting *out* of it. Removing that property opts you back in.\n\n**Other considerations:**\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| CLI | Use `dotnet test` (still works) or `dotnet run` on the test project directly |\n| VS integration | Ensure VS 17.10+ for full Test Explorer support |\n| CI | Replace any `vstest.console.exe` invocations with `dotnet test` |\n| Runsettings | Most `.runsettings` options have equivalents; some need migration to CLI args or code config |\n\nIf you use any VSTest-specific adapters or custom `.runsettings` heavily, review the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) for adapter replacements.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9939241f-7604-489d-9120-bc3324e072a2","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"E839:32B862:26953F6:290C60B:6A0493B4"},"id":"6b930ff1-4eb0-4d43-a4bf-7d3fe40c6c23","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:07:45.928Z","parentId":"084ccba4-228f-44b4-b18e-aa27ce5b22ab"}
